@Andrzej
The word "arena" comes from the Latin "(H)arena" (with or without the "h"), which literally means "sand," and by extension, the sand on which sporting events (including gladiatorial games) were held. Hence the more limited usage in Polish, I'd guess. Latin probably borrowed "Harena" from Etruscan, a non-Indo-european language.

(Old news to many.)

